{
  "texts": [
    "These considerations might restrict the use of existing seq2seq models in such scenarios 32.",
    "We envision that EchoGPT could be used as a reporting interface, or a co-pilot that could generate echo reports with various inputs 48.",
    "EchoGPT inherits the limitations of LLMs, including hallucination 13, 18, 49.",
    "Although the number of hallucinations improved after the fine-tuning process, additional efforts such as optimization for factual correctness 43 or paired with a retrieval augmented generation system 50 are still required to minimize hallucinations before clinical implementation.",
    "Our study successfully built EchoGPT through QLoRA fine-tuning of open-source LLMs, and demonstrated that the model is capable of generating echocardiography reports on par with cardiologists, marking an advancement in integrating LLMs into current echo practice."
  ]
}